sentences: Lucius Carl Watters (December 19, 1911 – November 5, 1989) was a trumpeter and bandleader of the Yerba Buena Jazz Band.
In 1925, he moved with his family to San Francisco, where he started a jazz band.
During the 1930s, he went on tour across America with the Carol Lofner big band.
In 1938, he formed a band that included Hayes, Helm, Squire Gersh, Bob Scobey, and Russell Bennett.
In 1939, he established the Yerba Buena Jazz Band to revive the New Orleans jazz style of King Oliver.
The band performed at the Dawn Club in San Francisco.
It went on hiatus in 1942 when Watters entered the U.S. Navy but reunited at the Dawn after World War II.

After the Dawn closed, the band started the club Hambone Kelly's in El Cerrito, California.
In 1949 the band performed with visiting musicians Kid Ory, James P. Johnson, and Mutt Carey.
After Hambone Kelly's closed, the band broke up in 1950.
In 1963, he came out of retirement to perform with Murphy at an anti-nuclear protest in California to prevent a nuclear plant from being constructed at Bodega Bay.
In 1961, a mineral from California was named wattersite in his honor.
